books.author: Edith Hamilton
books.title: Mythology: Timeless Tales of Gods and Heroes
books.description: A classic collection of stories from Greek, Roman, Norse, and Egyptian mythology, featuring gods, heroes, monsters, and adventures.

books.author: Jared Diamond
books.title: Guns, Germs, and Steel
books.description: A Pulitzer Prize-winning book that explores how geography, climate, and natural resources shaped the development and diversity of human civilizations.

books.author: William L. Shirer
books.title: The Rise and Fall of the Third Reich
books.description: A comprehensive and authoritative account of the rise and fall of Nazi Germany, based on the author’s firsthand experience as a journalist and witness.

books.author: Peter Frankopan
books.title: The Silk Roads
books.description: A sweeping and revisionist history of the world, focusing on the importance and impact of the ancient trade routes that connected East and West.

books.author: Walter Isaacson
books.title: Steve Jobs
books.description: A biography of the visionary and charismatic co-founder of Apple, based on interviews with Jobs and his family, friends, and colleagues.

books.author: Malala Yousafzai and Christina Lamb
books.title: I Am Malala
books.description: A memoir of the youngest Nobel Peace Prize laureate, who survived a brutal attack by the Taliban for her advocacy of girls’ education in Pakistan.

books.author: Betty Friedan
books.title: The Feminine Mystique
books.description: A groundbreaking book that sparked the second wave of feminism, exposing the dissatisfaction and oppression of women in postwar America.

books.author: Malcolm X and Alex Haley
books.title: The Autobiography of Malcolm X
books.description: A powerful and influential memoir of the civil rights activist and Muslim leader, who challenged racism and injustice in America.

books.author: J.K. Rowling
books.title: Harry Potter and the Philosopher’s Stone
books.description: A fantasy novel about a young boy who discovers that he is a wizard and enters a magical world of adventure and danger.

books.author: Douglas Adams
books.title: The Hitchhiker’s Guide to the Galaxy
books.description: A sci-fi comedy novel about a hapless Earthling who hitchhikes across the galaxy with an alien friend after the planet is destroyed.
